<doc id="79931" url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=79931" title="Baptes">
Baptes

The Baptes (Greek βάπτης) were priests of the Greek goddess Cottytus. The word comes from the Greek verb βάπτω ("baptō"), meaning "to dip in water". The Baptes practised obscene ceremonies at night; they included orgies so hedonistic that even Cottytus herself was disgusted.
